sentence: Tuesday's session closes with the NASDAQ Composite Index at 3,237.86.
The total shares traded for the NASDAQ was over 1.47 billion.
Declining stocks led advancers by 1.21 to 1 ratio.
There were 1119 advancers and 1355 decliners for the day.
On the NASDAQ Stock Exchange 43 stocks reached a 52 week high and 13 those reaching lows totaled.
The most active, advancers, decliners, unusual volume and most active by dollar volume can be monitored intraday on the Most Active Stocks page.
The NASDAQ 100 index closed up .67% for the day; a total of 18.54 points.
Dollar Tree, Inc. ( DLTR ) had the largest percent change down (-2.21%) while Microsoft Corporation ( MSFT ) had the largest percent change gain rising 3.57%.
The Dow Jones index closed up .41% for the day; a total of 59.98 points.
Procter & Gamble Company (The) ( PG ) had the largest percent change down (-.67%) while Microsoft Corporation ( MSFT ) had the largest percent change gain rising 3.57%.
